    coursesFeesDetailed: 'Programme: BBA (General), BBA Honours, BBA Honours with Research, BBA Decision Science, BBA Applied Finance with FinTech, BBA Finance & International Business - all 3-year full-time (4th year optional for Honours with Research). Total tuition fee (2026-27): approximately INR 8.25 Lakh for the 3-year General/Honours BBA; total academic fee including one-time charges ≈ INR 8.33 Lakh. Dual-specialisation tracks such as Finance & International Business run higher, roughly INR 2.6-2.8 Lakh per year (≈ INR 8-8.5 Lakh total). Honours with Research (4th year) adds approximately INR 3 Lakh, bringing the total to ≈ INR 11.3 Lakh. NRI/foreign-national quota fees are significantly higher - around INR 10.7-12.2 Lakh for the full course. First-year payment is typically the largest instalment, around INR 2.8 Lakh, with a one-time registration/admission fee of INR 8,000. Hostel fees (optional, Central Campus) range from roughly INR 42,000 to INR 1,12,000 per year depending on room type. Merit scholarships offering up to 50% fee waiver are available from the second year onward, based on CGPA (typically above 3.7/4), extracurricular participation and financial need.',
    admissionDetailed: 'Eligibility: Pass in Class 12 (any stream - Science, Commerce, Arts) from a recognised board; BBA Decision Science requires at least 60% with Maths/Statistics/Computer Science background. Step 1 - Online application through the official portal with a processing fee (≈ INR 1,500-8,000 depending on campus/programme). Step 2 - Christ University Entrance Test (CUET-Christ): a 120-question, 120-minute online test covering English, General Knowledge, Fundamental Accounting, Reasoning, Mathematics, and Data Analysis & Interpretation (+1 for correct, -0.25 for incorrect). Step 3 - Skill assessment including a Micro-Presentation (MP) of about 90 seconds on an assigned topic, testing communication and spontaneity. Step 4 - Personal Interview (PI) evaluating overall personality, aptitude and clarity of career goals. Final merit list combines CUET score, MP, PI performance and Class 12 academic record; results are typically announced within 10-12 days of the interview. International/NRI applicants (IB, GCE/Edexcel, etc.) are evaluated per AIU equivalence norms. Required documents: Class 10 & 12 mark sheets, transfer certificate, migration certificate (non-Karnataka boards), passport-size photographs, ID proofs, and (for NRI/foreign applicants) visa, passport and medical certificate copies.',
    placementsDetailed: 'Placement eligibility begins from the 5th semester onward, subject to a minimum CGPA of 6.0. Approximately 80-90% of registered/eligible BBA students secure offers through campus placements each year. 2025 batch average package: around INR 6-6.5 LPA across the general BBA cohort. The Honours stream, being smaller and research-oriented, attracts premium recruiters from consulting, investment banking, and technology, pushing highest packages well above INR 20-25 LPA in select cases. Placements are coordinated through the Centre for Professional and Career Guidance (CPCG), which runs resume-building workshops, mock interviews and aptitude training ahead of the placement season. Recruiters span consulting (BCG, McKinsey exposure at Honours level), Big-4 (Deloitte, EY, KPMG), banking/financial services (ICICI Bank, JP Morgan, Goldman Sachs), IT/consulting majors (TCS, Infosys, Accenture) and FMCG/consumer companies.',
    campusDetailed: 'Bangalore Central Campus is a fully residential, multi-block urban campus on Hosur Road with modern classrooms, libraries, seminar halls and Wi-Fi-enabled infrastructure. Dedicated hostel blocks for men and women (Central Campus), with tiered room options and mess facilities; hostel registration fee ≈ INR 300 in addition to room charges. Active student life: Finance Club, Oratory Club, Entrepreneurship Club, Marketing Club, Debate Club and numerous inter-collegiate fests, with strong opportunities to organise/lead events. Year-long internship component embedded into the BBA (Honours) structure, alongside industry guest lectures and live projects. On-campus bank branch to assist with education-loan processing; instalment-based fee payment available for amounts above INR 10,000. Multiple campuses (Bangalore Central, Kengeri, Yeshwanthpur, Delhi-NCR, Lavasa) allow programme delivery at different fee points and settings.',
    cutoffDetailed: "Admission is not based on a fixed cutoff percentage but on composite merit across CUET score, Micro-Presentation, Personal Interview and Class 12 marks. Out of roughly 10,000 applicants for the flagship BBA Finance & International Business stream, only about 480 seats are offered - an acceptance rate near 5%. BBA Honours seats are even more limited (around 120), making it one of the most competitive UG business programmes in India. Karnataka PUC candidates and those from CBSE/ICSE/State boards compete on a common merit list; strong Class 12 academic performance materially improves selection odds. Results/selection outcomes are typically communicated 10-12 days after the interview round, with admission confirmed upon fee payment by the stipulated deadline.",
