    coursesFeesDetailed: 'Programme: BBA across seven specialisations (Corporate; Finance & Accounting; Entrepreneurship/WOW; Sports Management; Strategic Finance with US CMA; Branding, Advertising & Events; Entertainment & Media Management) - 3-year full-time. Total tuition fee: reported figures range from roughly INR 6.75 Lakh to as high as INR 12-16 Lakh depending on specialisation and source; the ACCA/CMA-integrated tracks sit at the premium end. First-year fee is typically around INR 3.15 Lakh for the standard BBA track. BBA in International Finance (ACCA-UK integrated): first-year fees around INR 85,000, with total tuition near INR 2.42 Lakh across all semesters for the base component (additional ACCA exam/registration fees apply separately). A one-time registration fee of approximately INR 25,000-30,000 is generally payable at admission. Online BBA (Jain Online, UGC-DEB recognised) is available at a much lower cost - roughly INR 1.5-2.55 Lakh total, aimed at working professionals or distance learners.',
