    cutoffDetailed: "No single published numeric cutoff - admission is determined by SJUET score combined with Personal Interview performance, though the commonly cited eligibility floor is a high 80% aggregate in Class 12. Given the entrance-test-plus-interview format, actual selection intensity varies by specialisation and yearly applicant pool rather than a fixed rank list. SJUET results and subsequent interview call-outs are typically released within a few weeks of the test date, per cycle (e.g., Cycle 1 in January). Final admission confirmation requires document verification and fee payment within the notified deadline.",
