    overviewDetailed: "MCC offers B.Com in several tracks including a straightforward general programme, a Business Analytics specialisation (requiring a Maths/Stats/CS background), an Investment Banking specialisation, and the flagship B.Com International Accounting & Finance (IAF), integrated with the UK ACCA qualification (13 papers, with 6 exemptions built into the degree). Admission to standard B.Com is purely merit-based with no entrance exam or interview, but competition is intense given MCC reputation and central Bengaluru location.",
    coursesFeesDetailed: 'Programme options: B.Com (General), B.Com International Accounting & Finance (ACCA-integrated), B.Com Professional, B.Com Investment Banking, B.Com Business Analytics — all 3-year full-time under Bengaluru City University affiliation. Total B.Com (General) fee: approximately INR 2.95-4.4 Lakh depending on specialisation. B.Com International Accounting & Finance (2026-27): total academic fee ≈ INR 4.4 Lakh (tuition ≈ INR 4.22 Lakh, caution fee INR 6,000, other fees INR 12,500); first-year payable ≈ INR 1.48 Lakh — a steep rise from ≈ INR 2.95 Lakh in 2025. B.Com Professional and Investment Banking specialisations: total fees around INR 3.91 Lakh. Approximate annual fee for standard B.Com is reported around INR 1.22-1.4 Lakh. Additional eligibility fees (INR 0-73,400) apply based on board/state background. German/French language options add ≈ INR 4,500. Scholarships available for low-income families and high academic performers.',
