    placementsDetailed: '2025 placement report (overall UG): highest package INR 24.8 LPA, average package INR 5.5 LPA, median package INR 4.8 LPA. 586 undergraduate students placed in a recent cycle across all programmes, including B.Com. B.Com International Accounting & Finance placements begin from the 4th semester (2nd year), with recruiters including Google, Deloitte and EY drawn specifically to the ACCA-integrated cohort. MCC placement office enforces a strict one offer per student policy (with a limited exception for offers ≤ INR 2 LPA), and mandates formal, business-attire recruitment participation. Final-year students need a minimum 60% aggregate with no active backlogs to register for placements, plus mandatory attendance at recruitment training (75%+) and practice assessments (80%+ completion). B.Com and BBA are highlighted by MCC as offering the strongest placement ROI among the college programmes.',
    campusDetailed: 'Centrally located on Palace Road, Vasanth Nagar — Bengaluru CBD, close to Vidhana Soudha and major corporate hubs. Well-maintained hostels (on-campus, historically for women; now transitioning with co-education at UG level from 2024), architecturally notable buildings, and a large well-stocked library. Free doubt-solving sessions offered by faculty for the ACCA-integrated B.Com IAF cohort, alongside highly qualified faculty combining academic and corporate experience. Modern classrooms with up-to-date equipment; dedicated placement cell running mock interviews and resume-building workshops. UGC Potential for Excellence status, DBT Star College status, and DSIR SIRO recognition, indicating institutional strength beyond teaching alone.',
    cutoffDetailed: 'Reported admission cutoffs for standard B.Com run approximately 75-80%+ in the qualifying board exam; the International Accounting & Finance (ACCA) specialisation commands a distinctly higher bar, with Accountancy-subject marks weighted heavily in the merit calculation. Because admission is purely merit-based (no entrance test/interview for standard B.Com), cutoffs are a hard determinant — students below the threshold are not admitted regardless of other qualifications. Where the provisional cutoff is not met, MCC may fall back on an aptitude test plus joint interview as an alternate route, though this is not guaranteed and is used selectively. Given intense competition for limited seats in Bengaluru central campus location, cutoffs have trended upward in recent cycles, particularly for the ACCA-integrated track.',
