    overviewDetailed: "Kristu Jayanti B.Com is explicitly positioned, alongside MBA, as the university flagship programme, with strong international professional-body integration — ACCA (UK), CMA (US), CPA (US) and SAP certifications are offered as add-ons within several B.Com specialisations, including a dedicated B.Com Professional Accounting track and a B.Com integrated-with-ACCA programme. Admission is straightforward and merit-based, with no mandatory written entrance exam for the standard B.Com pathway.",
    coursesFeesDetailed: 'Programme: B.Com (General), B.Com Professional (Accounting), B.Com integrated with ACCA, B.Com with CMA/CPA/SAP add-ons — 3-year full-time. Total B.Com fee range (2026): approximately INR 3.3-7.6 Lakh depending on specialisation and duration, with the ACCA/CMA/CPA-integrated tracks at the higher end. Regular B.Com fee has been reported by students as low as INR 70,000/year in some cohorts (≈ INR 2.1 Lakh over 3 years), though official 2026 figures place the range higher (INR 3.3L-7.6L total) reflecting recent fee increases. Registration and examination fees for professional certifications (CA, ACCA, CMA, CPA, CFA) are charged separately by the respective professional bodies and are NOT included in KJC programme fees. Non-Karnataka-PU-board students may incur additional fees (reported INR 10,000-1.1 Lakh) beyond the base tuition. Admission registration fee: INR 5,000 (non-refundable); application processing fee: INR 1,000 (non-refundable). Scholarships include a standard B.Com scholarship of INR 10,000 for eligible students and the Jayantian Determination Scholarship (INR 20,000) for Divyangjan (differently-abled) students.',
