    placementsDetailed: 'As per NIRF 2025 data, roughly 710 UG (3-year) students were placed out of the graduating cohort, with a median package around INR 6.41-7.17 LPA. 70+ companies visited in the 2024-25 placement cycle, achieving an estimated 85% UG placement rate. Recruiters specifically named for Commerce/B.Com graduates include Deloitte, Morgan Stanley, KPMG, Wipro, EY, Grant Thornton, Amazon and Cognizant, alongside BFSI names like ICICI Bank and Federal Bank. The Centre for Employability and Corporate Relations (CECR), supported by a Talent Transformation Team (TTT), runs mock interviews and structured training ahead of placement season. Faculty strength is notable — over 1,500 faculty members overall, with 500+ being KJC alumni, many holding advanced degrees and industry experience, particularly relevant to the ACCA/CMA/CPA-integrated commerce tracks.',
    campusDetailed: '9.5-acre green campus in Kothanur, Bengaluru, with library access to over 100,000 books and 48,000+ e-journals — a strong resource base for Commerce research and CA/ACCA/CMA exam preparation. Separate hostels for men and women managed by a religious congregation; hostel fees reported around INR 70,000-1,00,000/year. Modern, tech-enabled classrooms and multiple auditoriums supporting the 300-400 lectures/semester demanded by the ACCA-integrated track. Strong international accreditation profile (NAAC A++, ACBSP-USA) underpinning the credibility of its ACCA/CMA/CPA/SAP-integrated B.Com pathways. Campus culture is described by some students as disciplined/strict, with limited informal mixed socialising — a trade-off some weigh against strong academics and international-certification opportunities.',
    cutoffDetailed: 'No fixed written-exam cutoff for standard B.Com — admission runs on merit counselling using the Class 10/12 score, with a minimum eligibility floor of 40% aggregate. The ACCA-integrated B.Com track effectively raises the practical bar given its additional interview round and heavier weighting on Accountancy performance at the PUC/12th level. India Today 2024 ranked KJC 54th nationally in Commerce, which can serve as a rough proxy for its relative competitive standing versus peer B.Com programmes in the city. Counselling and merit-list rounds for UG programmes typically run from around December through the admission deadline the following year, with multiple rounds as seats are filled.',
