    placementsDetailed: 'Placement rate: 85-90%. Highest package: ₹12-27 LPA. Average package: ₹6.5-8 LPA. Median package: ₹5 LPA. Top recruiters: Amazon, Deloitte, Accenture, ICICI Bank, HDFC Bank, Infosys, TCS, Tech Mahindra, EY, ITC, Byju\'s, Godrej, KPMG, Nike, Pantaloons, Capgemini, JP Morgan, Morgan Stanley, Berger Paints, Reliance Industries, Aditya Birla Group. 100% internship opportunities for all students with stipends ranging widely. PPO conversion rate strong. Roles offered: Business Development Executives, Management Trainees, Financial Analysts, Marketing professionals. Dedicated Placement Cell with career counselling and soft-skill development.',
    campusDetailed: '3-acre campus in Peenya Industrial Area, Bangalore with modern infrastructure. Facilities include ICT-enabled smart classrooms, well-equipped computer labs, library with vast collection and digital resources, seminar halls for conferences and workshops, sports facilities (indoor and outdoor), cafeteria, and research spaces. Separate hostel for boys and girls with Wi-Fi, 24x7 security, and mess. International collaborations with University of California, Riverside and ICD Business School, France for student exchange and global exposure. Global certification programs available.',
    cutoffDetailed: 'Karnataka PGCET rank considered for government quota seats. Management quota: minimum 50% in Bachelor\'s degree + valid entrance exam score. Merit-based scholarships including Smt. Nagarathnamma Scholarship (up to 100% fee waiver for top achievers). Final selection based on entrance score (50%) + academic profile (30%) + interview (20%).',
