    admissionDetailed: 'Step 1 — Register on the S-VYASA admissions portal (applynow.svyasa.edu.in). Step 2 — Download and complete the application form; submit along with required documents (mark sheets from Class 10 onward, two passport-size photographs, and a health/fitness certificate). Step 3 — Appear for the relevant entrance exam: KCET or CUET UG for B.Tech, BCA, BSc, BBA, B.Com; CAT/XAT/MAT/CMAT for MBA (followed by GD and PI); CUET PG or merit-based selection for MSc and MCA. Admission to most UG courses is merit-based on qualifying exam scores. Karnataka-domicile candidates with strong KCET/12th-grade marks may receive fee reductions. MBA admission specifically requires clearing CAT/XAT/MAT/CMAT followed by GD and PI.',
    placementsDetailed: 'The university maintains a placement department providing assistance, internships, and job-offer support, with a growing track record of industry connections. Select programmes have reported packages up to INR 25 LPA. B.Tech CSE (Cybersecurity) placement rate is reported around 80% by students, with an average package of INR 4.5-6 LPA; recruiters include TCS, Wipro, Infosys and Amazon. M.Sc in Clinical Psychology graduates typically start around INR 3-4 LPA, rising to INR 10-15 LPA with experience. The university research collaborations (e.g., with NIMHANS on schizophrenia, migraine and dementia studies) also create research-assistant pathways for graduates interested in academia.',
