    overviewDetailed: "ISI Bangalore is one of ISI extension centres (headquartered in Kolkata) and is particularly known for its B.Math programme — a highly theoretical, research-oriented Mathematics degree where a large share of graduates pursue higher studies abroad rather than immediate employment. The centre also offers MSc, MLibISc and PhD programmes, and — through a distinct offering — the increasingly popular Bachelor of Statistical Data Science (BSDS), which has a more industry/placement-oriented profile.",
    coursesFeesDetailed: 'Programme range: B.Math (3 years), BSc(Hons)/BSc Stat, MSc, M.Lib.I.Sc., PhD — offered across UG, PG and doctoral levels at the Bangalore Centre. B.Math: no course fee is charged; all admitted students receive a monthly scholarship (reported around INR 3,000/month), continued based on maintaining average marks and attendance. General course fees across most ISI Bangalore programmes range between approximately INR 11,000 and INR 70,800 total, reflecting the heavily subsidised, government-funded nature of the institute. Bachelor of Statistical Data Science (BSDS) — a separate flagship-style course — carries a notably higher total fee of approximately INR 8 Lakh. PG/Masters-level students (MSQMS, MSQE, etc.) typically receive a monthly stipend of INR 3,000-5,000.',
    admissionDetailed: 'Step 1 — Online application via the official ISI admissions portal (admission.isical.ac.in); application windows for most programmes open around mid-February and close in mid-March, with BSDS opening later (late April to late May). Step 2 — ISI Admission Test: a written test assessing mathematical and analytical aptitude, held at multiple centres nationally. Step 3 — For qualified/shortlisted candidates, a Personal Interview may follow depending on the programme. Final selection is based on weighted combination of Admission Test score and Interview performance. BSDS admission specifically uses CUET/JEE Main scores. Eligibility varies by programme: B.Math typically requires strong Class 12 performance in Mathematics/Physics/Chemistry. International students are eligible to apply.',
    placementsDetailed: '2025 placement brochure reported packages ranging from approximately INR 20.73 Lakh to INR 30 Lakh for placed students. Historical data indicates highest packages around INR 30-39 LPA and average packages of approximately INR 8-12 LPA for cohorts that participate in placements. Because B.Math is heavily theoretical, only around 25-30% of B.Math students typically sit for placements — the majority pursue higher studies (often abroad). By contrast, nearly all MSQMS/MSQE (Master-level, more applied) students participate in placements, with recruiters focused on data mining, machine learning, and statistical roles. Recruiters include Amazon, Maybank, PayPal, Uber, Tata Digital, Philips and Foodworks. Average internship stipends are reported around INR 15,000-30,000 per month.',
    campusDetailed: 'Spacious, green 30-acre campus with hostels, an auditorium, clubs, well-equipped laboratories, a cafeteria, and sports facilities. Located at 8th Mile, Mysore Road — accessible via Jayaram Das Factory Bus Stop (500m) and Jnana Bharati Halt railway station (1.6km); roughly 1.5 hours from Bangalore International Airport. Small, tight-knit student population (historically around 230-250 students across programmes at this centre), fostering close faculty-student interaction typical of ISI research culture. Strong alumni network concentrated in academia (professors and academicians in India and abroad), reflecting the institute research-first orientation, alongside a smaller but growing industry-facing alumni base.',
    cutoffDetailed: "ISI Bangalore does not publish a fixed numeric cutoff; admission is based on a weighted combination of Admission Test performance and Interview scores, and varies year to year depending on applicant pool strength. The B.Math admission bar is widely regarded as extremely high given the institute small intake and reputation as one of India most theoretically rigorous mathematics programmes. For BSDS (CUET/JEE Main-based route), cutoffs are influenced by seat availability and applicant volume in a given cycle rather than a single published percentile threshold. Given the institute tiny cohort size and national (rather than regional) applicant pool, ISI Bangalore admissions are among the most selective of all institutions covered.",
